Governor of Nasarawa State, Abdullahi Sule, has confirmed 13 new cases of COVID-19 in the state. Sule announced this during a press briefing, on Friday. He added that out of the 78 samples taken by NCDC, 13 returned positive. “Out of the 13 new cases of COVID-19, four had close contact with the late House of Assembly member, Sulieman Adamu, who died of coronavirus. “The other nine new cases were returnees from Lagos and Kano States.” This brings the total number of cases in the state to 25 with one death. Coronavirus: Gov. Abdullahi Sule not on self-isolation - Aide Nasarawa govt confirms another two COVID-19 cases COVID-19: Nasarawa state govt takes major action as coronavirus hits Abuja